Valerie Abou Chacra is not only a "Queen" in Lebanon's eyes, but she's a queen in her doting boyfriend Rabee' Moqbel's eyes as well. 
The 23-year-old was crowned Miss Lebanon 2015 on Tuesday, beating beauties Jocelyne Mosleh, Cynthia Samuel, Nour Nasrallah and Maria Tannous to the title. 
Photo: Facebook. 
Rabee' was by Valerie's side when she claimed the title of "most beautiful woman in Lebanon," and was quick to post pictures of his long-term girlfriend on social media. 
Photo: Al Jaras Magazine. 
In one of the photos, Rabee' proudly commented, "Behind every King, there's a Queen. I'm so proud of you. You're my everything." 
As for Valerie, she posted her own adorable snapshot with Rabee' and captioned it, "My number one." 
Photo: Al Jaras Magazine. 
But of course, Valerie didn't forget about her supportive family and posted this Facebook photo saying, " I would like to thank my family for their support and encouragement, because if it wasn't for them I wouldn't have achieved this level of success on my own. They are the reason why I was committed to getting this crown; I am more than blessed to make them proud. Family is all that matters. Through thick and thin, support is our mission. #MissLebanon2015 #FamilyFirst ."
